        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 5:27PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 526 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles west of Trion to near Fort Payne.
Movement was southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Little River Falls, New Moon, Broomtown, Fullerton, Chesterfield, and
Little River Canyon NP.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
northeastern Alabama.</instruction>
